observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Municipal Mayor require the:
designated GSO and Municipal Accountant to review the policies and procedures for Inventories, making sure that Chapter 7 of the LGU NGAS Manual is strictly adhered;
Municipal Accountant to refrain from recognizing inventories as outright expense to ensure that balances presented in the financial statements fairly represent the transactions that occurred in accordance to the relevant principles and method;
designated GSO and Municipal Accountant to strictly and regularly reconcile their inventory records; and
designated GSO to prepare the SSMIs and to conduct periodic physical count of inventories in order to prepare and submit the RPCI, as required by Sections 121 and 124 of the Manual, to properly account for the remaining inventory balance at year end.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor:

strictly require the Municipal Accountant to prepare bank reconciliation statements in an opportune time for all funds (current and time deposit accounts); 

instruct the Municipal Accountant and Municipal Treasurer to reconcile their respective records regularly;

exercise LGU’s authority granted under Section 74 and 111 of P.D. 1445 until they are able to prepare and submit bank reconciliation statements for all funds to the COA Audit Office concerned;

direct the Municipal Accountant and Municipal Treasurer to investigate and validate the confirmed balance of the LGU’s Time Deposit with the management of LBP; and 

enforce all rights and possible stringent legal action to require the LBP to account and return to the coffers of the Municipal Government of Bombon the amount asserted by the LGU plus all interests due which the LBP denied.

We recommended that Management:

send demand letters to the concerned AOs to enforce the liquidation of their cash advance;

require the Accountable Officers concerned to settle/liquidate immediately their outstanding cash advances and the concerned officials to strictly adhere to the rules and regulations on the granting, utilization and liquidation of cash advances provided under COA Circular 97-002;

enforce the appropriate sanctions provided by rules and regulations upon failure by the concerned AOs to liquidate their cash advances despite receipt of the demand letter issued by the Municipal Accountant;  

ensure that outstanding cash advances are liquidated prior to separation from office by any appointed or elected officer or employee; otherwise the personnel who signed the clearance will be held accountable for the liability of the official or employee who separated from the service.

