We recommended and Management agreed to:
a. Direct the GFPS Executive Committee and Technical Working Group to revisit the GAD Code of the Municipality for the prioritized  programs, projects and activities which were considered gender responsive to the concerns of the people of Bombon;
b. Institutionalize a GAD database and keep it abreast with the current status and needs of the community as to gender and development issues in order to facilitate the preparation of a relevant GAD Plan and Budget (GPB);
c. Require all the departments and offices in the Municipality to submit their respective GPB to the GFPS TWG not later than January of the preceding year for the timely preparation of the consolidated GPB for submission to the province in March of the same year; and
d. Finally, management shall submit a copy of the annual GAD Plan and Budget to the COA Audit Team within five (5) days from the receipt of the approved plan from DILG. Likewise, a copy of the GAD Accomplishment Report shall be furnished to the team within five (5) days from the end of January of the preceding year.

